Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1009 "The \NLost Article That Smells Like a Case"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.83,0:00:05.23,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,This way. It's over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.80,0:00:10.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I found this bracelet beneath these shrubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.25,0:00:12.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.81,0:00:17.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed that you spotted \Nsomething down here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.25,0:00:20.33,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I took a peek because I heard a kitty meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.52,0:00:22.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I found this on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:24.70,DCMain,MTISHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.45,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But this looks pretty expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.45,0:00:30.69,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's got a jewel or something on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.69,0:00:33.04,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a garnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.04,0:00:34.79,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.09,0:00:39.97,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.70,0:00:41.88,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.80,0:00:44.60,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.60,0:00:46.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.49,0:00:50.52,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we return this \Nbracelet to whoever lost it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.84,0:00:55.33,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea. That sounds like \Na job for the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.33,0:00:58.07,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But how are we going to find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.09,0:01:02.36,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find the store \Nthat sells that bracelet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:05.52,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,we should be able to find whoever lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.48,0:01:09.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.14,0:01:11.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.42,0:01:12.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys are in big trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:15.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Their search for the owner of a \Nmissing item takes a surprising turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:16.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.73,0:01:18.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.62,0:01:21.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:08.95,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}The Lost Article That Smells Like a Case
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.36,0:03:06.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Lost Article That Smells Like a Case!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.62,0:03:12.83,Jewelry,SIGN GOLD ON BLACK,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko Jewelry
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:18.73,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I've seen this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:19.98,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:20.72,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.59,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,It might be one of our products.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.85,0:03:25.47,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:28.10,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Or it might not be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:36.61,DCMain,EMPLOYEE B,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we used to sell a similar design.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.99,0:03:41.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The initials S.Y. are on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:46.91,DCMain,EMPLOYEE B,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Since we didn't sell it, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:07.78,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't been able to find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.34,0:04:12.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is turning it into the \Npolice our only option?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.12,0:04:14.02,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:23.15,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.01,0:04:26.07,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the guy from the accessory shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:28.68,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked the other staff about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:32.71,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,one of them said they remembered the \Nperson who bought that bracelet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.06,0:04:34.54,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.70,0:04:37.84,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Their name is Yamaki Shinobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.84,0:04:41.09,DCMain,EMPLOYEE A,0000,0000,0000,,Since you've already got their bracelet, \Ncould you return it to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:42.31,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:43.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can count on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:51.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.40,0:04:54.02,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}All right. Let's ask if \Nthat bracelet is theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:57.58,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:01.04,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:04.90,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Um, can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:07.32,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, are you Yamaki Shinobu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:11.74,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Shinobu is my older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.65,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What? Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:15.58,Risa,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yamaki Risa (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.65,0:05:16.84,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, and? Do you have \Nbusiness with my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:25.69,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We found a bracelet that we believe \Nbelongs to your brother at the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.69,0:05:26.79,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.04,0:05:31.47,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,See? It's got the initials S.Y. on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.19,0:05:34.73,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely my brother's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:36.16,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:38.10,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We finally found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.59,0:05:41.73,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming all \Nthis way to return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:44.23,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yamaki Risa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:46.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where's your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:50.24,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Oh, he's out of the house right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.63,0:05:54.26,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return this bracelet to my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:55.55,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:05:56.89,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:05:58.12,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:05:59.52,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:02.24,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.24,0:06:04.59,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,It could be important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.08,0:06:05.83,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.98,0:06:10.14,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.94,0:06:13.20,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You smell wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:14.85,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Must be your perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.33,0:06:18.36,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. It's my favorite perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.36,0:06:19.51,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.64,0:06:26.33,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we were able to return \Nthe bracelet to its owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.33,0:06:29.36,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His sister was delighted, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:31.36,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That settles that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.36,0:06:32.47,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.21,0:06:34.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that Ran-neechan asked \Nme to run an errand for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:38.80,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.80,0:06:40.42,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:42.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:44.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Careful on your way home, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.22,0:07:18.04,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for visiting out of the blue, Oi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:21.42,Yutaka,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Oi Yutaka (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:21.54,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, it's fine. You're Yamaki-san's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.69,0:07:24.17,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm his sister Risa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.17,0:07:28.34,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I actually lost touch with \Nmy brother this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:29.19,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:33.18,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I visited his home, but he \Nhasn't been back in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.37,0:07:36.68,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's concerning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.03,0:07:42.68,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, these are the last messages \NI exchanged with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:44.06,Texts,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,When do you want to meet up? \N\NI'm eating with my friend Oi \Nnow. I'll call you tomorrow. \N\NGot it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:48.57,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we went out to eat that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.75,0:07:51.20,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,What was my brother like that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:53.95,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure how to answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:55.41,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Anything helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.67,0:07:58.06,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:08:01.96,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,he didn't have anything to drink \Nbecause he was meeting a friend later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.29,0:08:05.71,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who that friend was?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.90,0:08:09.32,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.32,0:08:10.47,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.47,0:08:14.57,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,But if Yamaki-san was meeting a friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.57,0:08:16.30,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,then it was probably Yagi or Kogure-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:17.85,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.11,0:08:19.11,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.11,0:08:20.69,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe you should meet with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.40,0:08:24.18,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you their addresses. Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:25.85,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.09,0:08:28.87,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure both of them live nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.81,0:08:49.33,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.33,0:08:51.71,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the errand Ran-san asked you to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:53.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.35,0:08:56.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.53,0:08:59.35,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you following Risa-oneesan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:04.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried if she'd actually \Nreturn the bracelet to her brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:08.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san's probably looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.18,0:09:09.02,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:11.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.61,0:09:14.68,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did she and her brother get into an argument?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:16.66,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.74,0:09:19.23,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.23,0:09:21.54,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. After all, Conan-kun \Nthinks it's suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:23.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, Risa-san's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.85,0:09:32.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. I lost her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.43,0:09:35.01,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.01,0:09:37.72,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:39.55,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:46.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san went to meet either her brother's \Nfriend Kogure-san or Yagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.45,0:09:48.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's split up and look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:49.56,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:55.32,Yagi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yagi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.71,0:09:55.32,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to disappoint you \Nafter you came all the way here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:58.61,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't see Yamaki-san that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.02,0:10:00.20,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.40,0:10:05.81,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But I don't think you need \Nto be so worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:07.08,Keita,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yagi Keita (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.81,0:10:10.14,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Actually, this was found at a park.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:12.46,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,My brother always wore this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.04,0:10:16.48,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Since this was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:19.57,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried my brother may have \Ngotten caught up in something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.57,0:10:20.80,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Have you contacted the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.47,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.92,0:10:26.03,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to talk to Kogure-san next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:27.10,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.38,0:10:32.13,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Very well. I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.13,0:10:34.03,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You must feel forlorn on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.03,0:10:37.11,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.39,0:10:40.61,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get ready to go right \Naway. Give me a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.61,0:10:41.37,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:44.24,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.78,0:10:47.62,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also worried about Yamaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:56.27,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We can't find her anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:57.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Genta-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.85,0:11:03.10,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,According to Conan-kun, Yagi-san's \Nhouse should be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:05.10,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:08.01,DCMain,SHIZU,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.01,0:11:12.37,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for the residence of Yagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:13.73,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where they live, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.90,0:11:17.36,Shizu,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kanno Shizu (65)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.04,0:11:17.59,DCMain,SHIZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yagi-san? Oh, Yagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.59,0:11:18.61,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You know them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.87,0:11:22.07,DCMain,SHIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He lives in this apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:35.34,Yagi2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yagi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:37.84,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.18,0:11:45.10,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.46,0:11:46.93,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:48.36,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for dropping in suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.36,0:11:51.98,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Yamaki Shinobu-san's friend Yagi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:54.28,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.28,0:11:55.98,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:57.82,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:12:00.33,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We're the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.33,0:12:03.93,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for a lady \Nnamed Yamaki Risa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.93,0:12:05.62,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did she come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.90,0:12:06.60,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:10.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san is Yamaki Shinobu-san's \Nyounger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.38,0:12:13.92,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She seems to be looking for her brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:18.04,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I was at home all day today, \Nbut nobody visited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.41,0:12:19.80,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.10,0:12:24.30,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Then she must be at Kogure's \Nplace where Conan went.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.65,0:12:26.94,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you know, get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:28.28,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.28,0:12:30.64,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-chan, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:31.64,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.30,0:12:35.54,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I couldn't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:39.32,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. Sorry for interrupting \Nyour busy schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.32,0:12:40.22,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.80,0:12:43.90,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.48,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe those kids are involved, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.64,0:13:00.96,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, man. This place was a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:02.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:05.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san must be where Conan-kun—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:07.26,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys. Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.71,0:13:10.22,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, how did things go over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.52,0:13:13.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.11,0:13:18.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,According to the neighbors, Kogure-san \Nhasn't been home since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.90,0:13:22.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san probably headed to Yagi-san's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:24.49,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:27.26,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't come here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.26,0:13:28.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:30.12,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:33.39,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think Yagi-san is lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.39,0:13:34.12,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.69,0:13:39.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I smelled Risa-oneesan at his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.05,0:13:41.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Ayumi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.64,0:13:43.76,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm sure I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.14,0:13:47.22,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It was the smell of her perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:51.39,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean she was at his place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.78,0:13:54.52,DCItalic,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:55.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:14:00.23,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There was something about Yagi-san's \Napartment that I found odd, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:04.90,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The shoes were tidily put away in \Nthe shoe cabinet at the entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:09.41,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,except for a pair of boots that seemed \Nto have been sloppily stuffed in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:12.30,DCItalic,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you suppose that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.30,0:14:14.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you guys right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.37,0:14:15.08,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:18.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,In front of Yagi-san's apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:19.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.32,0:14:22.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay where you are, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.45,0:14:23.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:25.80,DCItalic,AYUJMI,0000,0000,0000,,But what about Risa-oneesan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:29.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the boots Mitsuhiko \Nsaid were sloppily put away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.09,0:14:33.13,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? What about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.13,0:14:35.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since you guys suddenly showed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:40.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he probably hastily hid Risa-san's \Nshoes inside those boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.39,0:14:58.14,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.14,0:14:59.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:01.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san is still inside \NYagi-san's apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.86,0:15:02.54,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:05.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But why would Yagi-san do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:10.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because Risa-san brought \NYamaki-san's bracelet to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:14.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I found it odd when we \Nvisited Yamaki-san's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.59,0:15:17.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Risa-san didn't live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:20.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Her brother lived there alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:22.31,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.64,0:15:26.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was only a men's umbrella \Nin the stand in the entryway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.49,0:15:33.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was also a wilting houseplant \Nwith yellowing leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.02,0:15:39.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, her brother \Nhasn't been home in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.36,0:15:41.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then why was Risa-oneesan there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:45.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She probably went there because she \Ncouldn't get in touch with her brother
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.05,0:15:46.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and was worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:51.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But because we returned the bracelet to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:54.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she believed her brother may have \Ngotten swept up in something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.08,0:15:59.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The string on the bracelet \Nwas broken, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.67,0:16:05.13,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been torn off during \Nan argument with the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.13,0:16:10.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were tire tracks in the road in front of \Nthe park and what looked like bloodstains, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:18.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was Yagi-san who got into an \Nargument with Risa-san's brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:20.10,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.10,0:16:22.46,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you do, guys, stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.90,0:16:24.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do anything until I arrive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.81,0:16:32.58,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This wouldn't have happened to \Nyou if this hadn't turned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:36.76,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's your brother's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.76,0:16:41.45,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I had Yamaki-san fork over some money \Nbecause I had an opportunity to get rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.45,0:16:44.61,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But there were some problems, \Nand I lost it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.61,0:16:47.48,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yamaki-san was furious when he stormed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.71,0:16:52.19,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But that's how investments work, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.84,0:16:55.80,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes you win, and sometimes you lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.80,0:16:57.65,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's how investments work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.82,0:17:02.87,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But your brother insisted \Nthat I return his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.90,0:17:08.48,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I explained repeatedly that \NI couldn't right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:13.63,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but he was impatient and said \Nhe'd report me to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.67,0:17:17.77,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, he threatened \Nto tell my fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.87,0:17:21.11,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:26.19,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:31.98,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you to see your brother tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:33.57,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.57,0:17:35.17,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.17,0:17:36.95,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We can't wait for Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.14,0:17:37.96,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.96,0:17:41.20,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We should rescue Risa-oneesan ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.56,0:17:47.86,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if I hadn't found that \Nbracelet, this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.86,0:17:49.74,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:51.85,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's Yagi-san who's the \Nbad guy in this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.85,0:17:53.74,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.74,0:17:58.76,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if you hadn't found that bracelet, \Nwe wouldn't have identified the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:01.06,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.06,0:18:03.26,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.55,0:18:08.64,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ring the doorbell, and \Nwhile Yagi-san is distracted...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:11.27,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll jump out from behind \Nthe door and tackle him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:11.77,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.99,0:18:15.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go inside and rescue Risa-oneesan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:19.07,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The perfect plan, if I say so myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.61,0:18:22.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll settle this case before Conan arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.73,0:18:25.70,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can already see Conan-kun's \Ndisappointed expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:27.33,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.32,0:18:29.83,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Ayumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.11,0:18:32.71,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem with my plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.90,0:18:36.21,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Behind you. Mitsuhiko-kun, behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.42,0:18:38.23,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Behind me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.26,0:18:41.80,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you kids to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.31,0:18:45.47,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:47.23,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.49,0:18:48.92,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.92,0:18:53.49,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you kids get \Nfor playing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.49,0:18:55.53,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko-kun, close your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.54,0:19:00.70,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.72,0:19:05.95,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. I'll teach those \Nkids to screw with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.26,0:19:10.42,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, hurry, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.63,0:19:14.04,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It skipped our floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.04,0:19:16.30,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:19.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.12,0:19:22.93,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's another elevator over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:24.60,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.02,0:19:32.17,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.17,0:19:33.61,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:36.86,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The elevator is still on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:39.32,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:43.45,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, you'll get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:49.62,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:20:00.18,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:05.43,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:08.11,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The doors won't close while \NI'm holding them open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.42,0:20:14.08,DCMain,YAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, what should I \Ndo with you impudent kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.08,0:20:15.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Get down, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.80,0:20:31.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I made it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:40.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Later, an investigation \Nrevealed that the tire marks
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.41,0:20:42.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,in front of the park matched \Nthe tires of Yagi Keita's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:47.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The blood left there was also \Nfound to be Yamaki Shinobu-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.32,0:20:50.17,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.17,0:20:52.68,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,You saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.45,0:20:55.76,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:57.69,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:20:59.69,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.25,0:21:09.53,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.42,0:21:14.04,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,If not for this, my brother's \Ncase wouldn't have been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.74,0:21:21.72,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,No, he probably wanted it to be \Nsolved by you, the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.52,0:21:26.92,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Um, that gemstone is a garnet, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.92,0:21:30.31,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right. It's my birth stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.09,0:21:32.47,DCMain,RISA,0000,0000,0000,,My brother always...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.15,0:23:09.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:11.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I kept telling you guys not to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.77,0:23:13.24,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.24,0:23:14.92,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But, but, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.92,0:23:17.25,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys did good this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.83,0:23:19.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.74,0:23:21.25,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.88,0:23:26.13,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,I just found this over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.74,0:23:28.30,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this belong to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.83,0:23:31.65,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.65,0:23:33.21,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,A lost item?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.21,0:23:34.70,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.87,0:23:39.57,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,This is a job for the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.04,0:23:43.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't learned their lesson {\i0}at all{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.12,0:23:48.57,DCMain,YAMAZATO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Solve the dine and dashes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.82,0:23:51.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.06,0:23:53.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, at Beika Park...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:23:55.19,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.21,0:24:02.62,DCMain,YAMAZATO,0000,0000,0000,,Due to that string of incidents, the \Nsmile finally disappeared from her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.46,0:24:06.71,DCMain,YAMAZATO,0000,0000,0000,,Please solve this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:08.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Idol Whose Smile Disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.40,0:24:13.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NIdol Whose Smile Disappeared!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Red Shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.16,0:24:32.82,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.82,0:24:34.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Red shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:35.55,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.55,0:24:36.32,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.32,0:24:38.07,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Conan-kun, you're so good \Nat kicking your shoes off.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.07,0:24:39.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Just like a scarlet bullet.
